Text: I couldn't fight them...and I couldn't even get my authority back when it was stolen. So what good am I?
I need to find a way to be more useful.
I will dedicate myself first to healing magicks so I may help treat people's wounds.
It will be a time-consuming process to reacquire my abilities, but a necessary one that I dare not rush. Even though there's no telling when Calyx will make his next move...
Raha and Alphinaud patrol the city, while Y'shtola and Alisaie continue treating levin sickness and those injured in the attack.
I shall stay here to help coordinate efforts, so I suggest taking the opportunity to get some rest.
Come to check on things? Nothing of note has transpired since you left, although the body of that citizen remains unaccounted for...
As long as we keep Sphene's identity under wraps, it should be safe enough to walk around the city.
Still, we can't be too cautious while the simulant's off doing whatever it is she's doing. Do take care out there.
We've set up patrols outside, so I came back here to see how things are.

Unfortunately, although we stopped the rampaging hover cargos, now we have to deal with delays in electrope transport and slowdowns in production. The complications will likely continue for some time...
We've decided to keep the soldiers here armed to drive away any wild beasts that might wander too close to Everkeep.
But seeing as how people live in the area as well, we're taking turns patrolling it. We all have the code for emergency shutdown, so we can handle any surprises.
I can't remember the last time we've had a power outage... I'll have to check the equipment for any abnormalities.
I'm working on securing a route to the foundation sector. Please sit tight for a while.
Calyx is more clever than anyone has any right to be, but I'll sniff him out somehow. Just leave it to me.
For the time being, the plan is to send out rotating patrols while I attempt to determine exactly what happened with the King of Resolve's authority.

While a more comprehensive solution would be preferable, it's difficult to commit to anything knowing Calyx might've already accounted for the possibility... We've no choice but to be ready to respond in multiple ways at a moment's notice.
When one's peace and safety are threatened, dread and despair are a natural response.

For better or worse, I think the reason we've not seen wider unrest is because the people's memories were rewritten. Some believe their queen looks after them still, and that provides a measure of comfort in troubled times.
Near the settlement? Understood─we'll head out at once.
Now that construction is complete, surely they could spare a moment to come and see me... \\<sigh> How long must I hold onto these blasted things?
Lamaty'i has been keeping me abreast of developments in Alexandria over linkshell.
I suspect it will be some time before its people know peace once more. Until then, I trust you will look after Lamaty'i and the young king.
I wonder how my friends in Tuliyollal are doing... We promised to play Triple Triad the next time I visit, so until then I'll practice hard and collect loads of rare cards!

Fair stranger! Do you wish to hear of the most splendorous event in the realm? Ah, something tells me you wouldn't have the faintest idea of what I speak. Let's converse anon, once you've seen a little more of this world.
In order to undertake this quest, you must first complete one of the following main scenario quests: “The Gridanian Envoy,” “The Ul'dahn Envoy,” or “The Lominsan Envoy.”
Thanks to your offering, this little one will hardly leave my side!
Navigatin's a seafarin' skill, but I'm happy to muck in an' help out on land with the logistics. As for the actual explorin', I'll leave that to ye!

Ketenramm might be shiftin' to the next phase of the expedition, but there's still plenty to do here─meteorological charts to study, provisions to source...the list goes on. Suffice it to say, I'll be keepin' busy until the expedition resumes.
After speaking with Alisaie, I asked Milos what he thought, and we decided to remove our regulators.
But then we heard the commotion outside, and...I didn't realize how vulnerable I would feel without a regulator...
I heard...what happened. You weren't hurt...were you?
The equipment here didn't start tryin' to kill me, but it did start actin' up while I was in the middle of my work!
One of my finest pieces, ruined─just like that! As if the power outage wasn't bad enough...
I was so swamped with work I barely made it to the funeral in time, so I didn't get a neo regulator.

But I suppose it was never an option in the first place, being from so far outside the city. No one around here got one, it seems, even though we all heard the broadcast telling us to register them...
Hunters are out there getting killed by bolts of lightning, and now us regular folks are being attacked by mechanical soldiers. Even Queen Sphene has abandoned us... What are we to do?
I heard stories of Queen Sphene's return, yet now some are saying she has left us once again...
Every whisper the wind brings rings ominous in my ears. Tread carefully, my friend.
The Brute Bomber will have vengeance at last! You're finished!
Oh, hello there, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. We've been taking turns patrolling outside, but there hasn't been any unusual activity from the machines.
Let's hope it stays that way...
The Landsguard is on high alert in the event of echo sightings.
Yak T'el remains clear for now, but rest assured we will contact you should the situation change.
No one will pass so long as I remain on guard here. You have my word.
If you're looking to travel to Gok Draak Descent, you need only ask and I'll see you on your way.
As you might imagine, a great deal of our work now involves processing applications for memory restoration, and consulting with those considering the procedure.
The mood in the city has certainly brightened of late. Perhaps you'd care to brighten yours with a pack or two of Angel Snacks? They're simply divine, I assure you!

What was that bloody broadcast all about? Just when I thought things had settled down... I tell ye, in times like these, I just wanna hop on my wheeler and speed through the city till my head's clear!
Been hearin' a lot about yer heroic exploits. I always thought my custom wheelers were the pinnacle o' style, but you, my friend, are somethin' else!
Now ain't the time to be mixing drinks... I need to pray...

All that nonsense with the neo regulators made me realize something─the here and now's more precious than some promised eternity. Whether it's a well-mixed drink or a chat with a customer, in the end, it's the simple things that matter.
I've been so anxious ever since that announcement in Resolution. I think a stiff drink's about the only thing that'd calm my nerves right now...
Queen Sphene's words really resonated with me... In the past, I used booze to cope when things got rough, but from now on I'll drink to celebrate life, not shy away from it!
With all that's happening, it's hard not to despair... But seeing Monom soldier on is keeping me on the strait and narrow.
Monom's been working like a Milalla possessed lately! Hearing about your exploits really got him fired up.
From foodstuffs to sundries, I stock just about anything you could need. I've even started selling a selection of Tuliyollan delicacies. My customers can't get enough of 'em.

Verifying registration number... Verification complete. Welcome, guest of Queen Sphene. This is Resolution, the operational center of Solution Nine. If you have any queries, please present yourself at the counter inside the facility.
I'm afraid there are no neo regulators left to issue...and I shall not be relinquishing mine under any circumstances.
I deeply regret my behavior during the upheaval... Thanks to you and your comrades though, I am now free of that malign influence.

In case you were wondering, this facility will henceforth help administer the memory restoration initiative. If you know of anyone in need of advice or assistance with their application, please do refer them to me.
My wife hasn't been the same since that broadcast. She spends every waking moment praying─to who or what, I'm not quite sure...
It feels like I've completely lost my wife... She's receiving treatment now, but will I get my beloved back at the end of it all?
My wife has finished her treatment at long last. It was a struggle at first, but she's made remarkable progress. I'm just relieved to see her smiling again!
If prayer is the key to eternal life, then I shall pray. Only prayer will bring salvation...
To tell you the truth, I'd had my fill of regulators, but here I am, about to apply for memory restoration. I'm ready to accept that life is finite─and all the more precious for it.
Rumor has it there are actually more than five thousand neo regulators in circulation. I don't know what to believe anymore...
When I heard Queen Sphene's broadcast, I felt a spark of hope return. She might not be the monarch we once knew, but those were the words of a queen who deeply cares for her people, no mistake.
Welcome back to Mosaic. Always happy to see my regulars, of which Queen Sphene has recently joined the ranks.
I cannot help but smile at the way she savors the coffee I brew for her.
Krrrzzzt... Emergency maintenance protocol in effect.
Current location: residential radius 9-14, section 01. Scanning visitor log... No entry detected for your registration number.
Current location: residential radius 9-14, section 02. Visitors must be equipped with a regulator or present a valid visitor permit.
My friend was talking about applying for memory restoration, but I don't think I'm ready to take the plunge. Who knows what might come flooding back...
It's strange how quickly things get back to normal. Still, I've come to appreciate the peace and quiet of these gardens in a way I never did before.
You're the one Sphene was talking about─the hero that saved Alexandria. Thanks doesn't quite do justice to what you did, but I'm afraid that's all I have.
A friend of mine had started wearing one of those neo regulators... Honestly, if it weren't for the ministrations of that kind Eldite woman, I fear I might have lost them forever.
Queen Sphene helped me realize it's the quiet joys and simple pleasures in life that matter most!

While trade with Tuliyollal has begun in earnest, the export of electrope-based goods remains heavily regulated. A pity, I know, but they would see little use outside of Alexandria without sufficient sources of lightning energies.
Feeling those hunger pangs, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>miss<Else/>sir</If>? Making sure we eat properly is important, especially in times like these!
Welcome, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>miss<Else/>sir</If>! It seems like only yesterday that you and Vow Wuk Lamat were here sampling my wares for the first time.
You know, we do get the occasional visitor from the dome. Strange folk, but nice enough. Everything's so different where they live that I never tire of hearing them talk about it.
I finally found the time to visit Hhusatahwi! Between the dance hall and the saloon, it's a wonder anyone ever goes home.
Everyone around town has been acting so strangely, it's hard to think straight... \\<sigh> Fancy drowning some sorrows with me?
Now's the time for a fresh start. I'll have a quick drink, then work like I've never worked before! Care to join?
I was heading out to fish as I usually do, when I ran into someone coming back from Everkeep. Seems they're playing some strange recording up there in Resolution...

I could hear that broadcast all the way out here in the outskirts. Even though it wasn't the same queen who listened to me talk about fishing, she had that same gentle way with words that always warmed my heart.
As you can see, I don't have a neo regulator. I'm terrified of dying...but there's not much I can do except continue to work.
Just as plants one day wither and die, our lives are destined to come to an end. It's important to cultivate what bounties we can while we have the chance.

I was over in Solution Nine on cleaning duty not long ago, and the way everyone's talking about those neo regulators has me worried... You don't suppose someone might have dropped one somewhere, do you?

It was you and your friends who fought to save us, wasn't it? I wish there was something I could do to repay you for all you've done, but I suppose all I have is thank you─thank you from the bottom of my heart.
Just when we believed the matter of rogue sentries was resolved, now the citizenry is in an uproar. Whatever their concerns may be now, it has naught to do with my research.

I never cared much for the idea of everlasting life. But in light of recent events, I came to realize there was a far more meaningful pursuit: protecting what life we have while it lasts. That is why I intend to devote my efforts to designing sentries that prioritize the safety of our people.
Out to stretch your legs, are you? We were just discussing the distribution of those neo regulators...
I've been told that other races should get precedence over mine since we live so long, but how is that fair? The idea of death is just as frightening for us as for anyone else.
Care to join us on our break? We were just thinking about what might be done now and what we can possibly do.
I know it's not much...but I feel we need to live our lives in a way that honors the friends who lost theirs.
I find losing myself in work helps calm me down a little. It never stops the thoughts entirely, though.
Once I've traded in these resources, I'll be donating the proceeds to the medical facility. People will be needing those services more than ever─not just now, but in the future as well.
A friend of mine in Everkeep mentioned something about a special recording playing up in Resolution. Sounds like it may be worth looking into.

I delivered some fresh vegetables to a friend in Everkeep not long ago. She went on and on about how delicious they were, and then the next thing I knew, she was in tears... I hadn't realized this whole ordeal had taken such a toll on her.
Everyone seems on edge as of late. I'm counting on a rich harvest to hopefully raise their spirits.
We managed to send off a fairly hefty load of produce today. More than enough to keep everyone healthy and happy, I'd say.

Queen Sphene came to visit us recently. She seemed mostly in good spirits, though I couldn't help but notice the way she regarded the ruins. It's hard to really know how much the old Alexandria meant to her.
I've noticed hunters have been equipped with better arms and armor of late, and no one ventures out alone anymore. With fewer spare souls to go around, you can never be too careful.
A lot's happened, and sure, some things have changed... But the essence of things doesn't change so easily.
We find what's been cast aside, gather it up, and give it new purpose. That's what we reforgers do best...and I reckon you're no different.

An acquaintance of mine recently underwent the memory restoration procedure, and they've been absolutely stricken ever since. Who could blame them, having to process the memories of their loved ones suddenly flooding back like that?
But no matter how much it hurt, they said it was worth it to remember all the happy times they shared together.
I finally took a trip beyond the barrier. Feeling the warmth of the sun on my skin and the baked earth under my feet─it was better than anything I'd ever dreamed of.
Now that Alexandria has awakened from its nightmare, I can get back to obsessing over Triple Triad. It's hard to enjoy your hobbies when you're in a constant state of anxiety, you know.
Here to see how the rroneek are doing? Don't worry, if anything were to happen to me, the machines would step in and tend to their needs.
It's funny... This lot have no idea what befell Alexandria, but they soon sensed my despair during the worst of it. How could you not love such perceptive creatures!
We apologize for the extended inconvenience. Please enjoy your time at the Bergmähr-Ring!
Greetings, valued visitor, are you experiencing distress? I am unfortunately unable to manifest Endless patrons at this time, but can otherwise provide any assistance you require.
Welcome to Canal Town! Without our gondolier present, gondola rides have been indefinitely suspended. Our beautiful streets, however, are always available for a delightful stroll!
The Dawnservants have ushered in a new age of prosperity for Tuliyollal. Their efforts should be commended!
Please, come in and rest a while. You're always welcome to rest here as long as you'd like.
I have been officially promoted to commander of the Landsguard. The seat had remained empty for a while, but...it was time.

My duties remain relatively unchanged, however. I will do my utmost to ensure the people of Tural can live in peace, and continue to hone my skills as a warrior...the memory of my predecessor ever present.
Preservation laboratories... I shudder to think at what they were researching, but this is no time to be squeamish.
An institute on Preservation's scale would have had many such facilities in the city. Yet I cannot help but wonder if this one is where my parents worked...
I'll share the method we used to find the containment complex once we're inside. It wasn't actually all that different to the story of how we stumbled across the Backroom.
Shale made me her assistant! She was teaching me the basics of “data management.”
It sounds like Gulool Ja played a big part in this breakthrough. I'll be sure to treat him to a fine feast once this is all over!
Going by the room labels on that map, we haven't entered any of the actual labs yet.
Not a single soul here besides us...
Another locked door. We could try the same card again, but...
This must be the door to the director's office. Go on! Try the card!
Looks like every room can be accessed from this hub.
It seems not everyone who joined Preservation became Endless right away. There must have been research that required physical bodies.
If there were others besides my parents who left Preservation, where might they be now...?
The scanner awaits. Hold the security card up to the panel and it should unlock the door.
What else do they have in this place? If I read that map right, it must be a lot smaller than the Yuweyawata facility...
Calyx hasn't bothered to show his face yet, I see. Maybe he hasn't noticed us? Or maybe he's just watching...and waiting.
How strange. This door is not lit up like the others.
Shouldn't the security card open this door as easily as the last one?
Hm, what does this sign say...?
What is it, Gulool Ja?
That Alexandria survived the war was in no small part thanks to the defensive measures developed by Preservation. In that regard, I shall always be grateful.
Everything we read in this place sings Calyx's praises. The people who worked here must have truly idolized him...
Yes! The door has power now!
Had his own body not been fated to fail him so young, would Calyx have pursued his Endless project with such fervor?
I don't expect to find any information on my parents in this next room, either. And that's something I can be proud of.
My earlier investigations put the data relay just past this door. Let's get it open, shall we?
Hearing Krile talk about her parents reminded me of how much I miss Namikka. I guess I'll never really get over it...
If that man in the recording was Director Demetrius, then this must be his office.
Was Calyx the one who gave orders to execute defectors? The more we learn about him, the less I understand...
Well, that went well. Excellent clue-finding, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>!
Great work, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! Leave it to you to divine passwords from an ornamental display!
We did it, thanks to you! And a little bit thanks to me, I hope?
Speaking of gemstone symbology... For Alexandrians, “sphene” holds the meaning of “eternal light.”
When my parents named me, it was with their wish that I become an unwavering beacon of hope for our people. To think on it now, I have ever shared that destiny with my other self.
Going up? One moment, and I'll send you on your way.
Are we in Jeuno...? I swear I was hunting colibri in Bhaflau Thickets not long ago.
I remember a bright light and then darkness... Then I think I heard someone ranting about how they failed, and echoes... It didn't really make sense.
\\<sigh> All that time putting together a party wasted... It's going to take forever to improve my closed position at this rate.
Ever since I got a hold of this staff, people finally stopped asking me to heal when we go hunting.
In fact, warriors and thieves have started timing their attacks to match my casting Flare. It's finally black mage's time to shine!
The area beyond this cave is currently impassable. It will be some time until the way through is cleared.
You wouldn't happen to know a game called Triple Triad, would you? Travelers passing through from Tuliyollal showed me the basics, but I feel like I've played it before.
Would you humor me with a match or two? I'm hoping that playing again will help me remember.
I can't remember much, but I'm sure that's no way to play. If you want to win, try thinking like those corsairs from the Near East─you have to be bold and take risks!
The moment I lost, I felt something stir within me, then I remembered. The game I was thinking of is similar to Triple Triad, but I didn't play it in Vana'diel. It was...somewhere else.
I can't remember where, exactly, but I know the game was just as fun as Triple Triad.
A draw, huh? Either you're going easy on me, or I'm better at this than I thought. I guess we'll have to go one more round to be certain.
I wonder what Otis and Zelenia would think of my becoming the queen of Alexandria as it is now.
Doubtless they would be pleased yet, knowing them, also beset by worry.
As their memory lives on inside me, so shall I strive to rule as if they advised me still─with a calm heart, and a mind open to counsel.
It is time we began a thorough investigation into the key and its capabilities. I've a feeling we'll be calling on your help in that endeavor ere all is said and done...
On a personal note, I should also like to learn more of the Milalla. The lore of the forgotten people will be indispensable in furthering my research.
Calyx demonstrated knowledge of both primal summoning and concepts. Discovering such techniques through independent study would be nigh on impossible, so we must assume he had a mentor...
But how are we to learn the identity of this beneficent teacher? Hopefully some hint is to be found amongst the remnants of Preservation's works.
We've compiled a summary of events and submitted our report to Ojika. As representatives of the Students of Baldesion, our thoughts and findings will also be shared with the Forum.
In less official matters, I am glad to see Krile find a satisfying end to her personal journey...though it appears her appetite for asking questions has only been sharpened!
I am most curious to see how Alexandria is welcomed upon the broader stage of nations.
As a heretofore unknown, technologically advanced country, I expect it will be met with considerable wariness. I shall do my humble best to ease the tension of the initial introductions.
The Alexandrians adopted our techniques so quickly that they no longer need our supervision to treat the enthralled.
You'd be surprised at how many porxie practitioners we've trained now. Angelo, too, has been looking rather proud of his efforts!
Thank you so much for helping us... I considered moving outside the barrier to keep Milos away from the lightning, but in the end, we decided to stay.
Even though he'll need regular treatments, he said there were things he wanted to do here, in Alexandria. I'm just happy to help him live out his dreams, no matter where we are.
My mother is all better! Sphene came by to check on us, and we talked about all kinds of things.
I told her I wanted to study hard and become a physician now, and it made her so happy!
Now that everything's peaceful again, there's not much for Oblivion to do, so I, uh...I've actually started a volunteer service to care for orphans.
There are so many children who have lost their parents, and if I could be for them what Geode was to me and Nostalgia, then... Well, everyone deserves to have a family.
I'll track him down as fast as I can, even if that means missing a little sleep. You'll be the first to know if we find anything.
We have our people out there evacuating the residents. I hope Geode isn't charging into trouble─he tends to lose sight of the big picture when lives are on the line.
I'm always the one sending others into danger, and all I can do is wait and hope for the best. Don't make me wait in vain, all right?
Y'shtola sent word ahead. You've done everything we could have asked for and more.
With Cahciua and Geode gone, I've become the default leader of Oblivion─a role for which I am woefully unsuited.

That said, the movement itself has little purpose now that Preservation is no more. Once things have settled down...well, once I've steeled myself for it, I should say...I might have to see about restoring my own memories on the quiet.
Seems the machines've gone quiet again, so I can get back to maintainin' the weapons around here. Hope for the best, but prepare for the worst, as they say!
What the bloody hells is goin' on out there!?
They brought back Geode's gun... Its rounds were spent an' its barrel was scorched, so ye can be sure he went down fightin'.
Pah, ye see all them frownin' faces? People need to clear their heads an' keep their hands busy.
That's how I get through each day, every day. Anyroad, it's back to work for me!
Don't ye be lettin' up now, ye hear? Let yer passion carry ye to the bitter end!
Made it back with all yer bits intact, eh? I knew ye was one to watch the moment I set eyes on ye!
As for me, there's all sorts o' restoration work comin' in. Won't be gettin' a proper snooze in for the foreseeable future, I reckon, ahahaha!
Day in, day out, just concentratin' on what's right in front o' me till I've crafted a piece I can be proud of... That's what life is all about!
Right! Back to it, then! These tools ain't goin' to hop up an' do the job themselves!
I've learned a lot about operating electrope machines, so I can keep helping Shale with her work!
I can't believe it... They're out of control again...
I know you can do this. And I'll be here keeping everyone's spirits up until you get back!
Hey, guess what!? The folks who quit the Daybreakers are all comin' back to us now!
Even those who got caught up in Wihuwte's crimes are sayin' they want back in─after they pay their dues, of course. Isn't that the best news you've heard all day!?
Look how happy Zekowa is now that our old friends are back to join us. That trouble with Wihuwte had really thinned the ranks.
I'm glad to have them back as well, of course! And with all the training we've been doing to improve our shooting, we'll never suffer under scum like Wihuwte ever again.
The Daybreakers and the Dustwatch are working hand in hand now. Not long ago, I would've laughed at the idea that our little group would be invited to attend town meetings.
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! The town's been a good sight quieter thanks to you.

Even Wihuwte is getting the chance to mend his ways─we put him under guard while he pitches in with the work around here. Judging by the sour looks he gives us, though, I don't think he's taken well to honest labor.
Good day, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>miss<Else/>sir</If>! As you can see, I am diligently repaying my debt to society!
I...oh, it's you. What, you think this is some kind of sideshow act I'm putting on for your entertainment? Go on, piss off!
Elene'shpya came by a while ago to give me a toy─a little ball of a thing with a face on it. He said it was a model of the actual machine Cahciua used to operate.

Seems his friends in the dome just went ahead and made dozens of them, and he all but begged me to take one off his hands. Well, I think it goes to show she was as much loved over there as she was here.
So only those wearing a neo regulator will be spared? That seems like something Queen Sphene should be opposed to...
When I heard Sphene's voice coming over that broadcast, it sounded so familiar and comforting.
Both the former and present Sphenes have the same way about them─their very presence gives hope to us all. Alexandria is in good hands, I think.
\\<sigh> I can't concentrate on work for the worry. The livestock couldn't give two shakes for what I think, though, so I'd best pull myself together...
After everything that's happened, I find myself tending the livestock and wondering what “life” really is...
...Ah, but why overthink it!? I may never know the meaning behind it all, but that doesn't change how much I love my work and my animals.
What's happened up in Everkeep? People have been acting awfully strange...

Even when the sentries turned violent, the authorities were able to keep the most essential machinery running. Avoiding interruptions to the food supply meant people still had the minimum necessary to go about their daily lives─someone in charge made a wise decision there.
The situation feels bleak, but I don't want to just flee the dome... We need to put our heads together, and think about what we can do to help.

When you rely on someone else for everything, like I have, you start wanting to blame them for anything that goes wrong. Well, enough's enough. From now on, I'll be taking responsibility for my own decisions.
Both Sphenes have been there when we needed them most. When I heard that heartfelt broadcast, I couldn't keep the tears from falling...
And you've risked your own life to fight on our behalf, too, haven't you? I don't know how to thank you for giving us a tomorrow to look forward to.
Come to check on us, have you? Things are calm enough around here, but the people in town sound...agitated. I hope nothing bad comes of it.
It was Sphene's calming voice which cut through the chaos, and bore us free of that suffocating darkness. At last, all is as it should be.
Thank you for taking a moment for Gulool Ja. He has experienced much hardship for one so young, and seems in a terrible hurry to grow up.
But I feel his future is a bright one. He has good friends to guide him if he missteps, and a hero to emulate in you.
I've heard they've begun restoring people's lost memories. Hopefully that means everyone will recall a certain Shetona I once knew.

She'd been wary of Zoraal Ja and his ambitions even from before the lands were fused─the last we ever saw of her was when she went off alone to infiltrate his military base. I wonder if that Eldite friend of hers remembers now...
When duties permit, I've been putting aside time to help train Gulool Ja. I know it's in his blood, but you should see how quickly he picks things up!
It's the idea of sparring with you that really spurs him along, though. It seems that day can't come fast enough!
\\<sigh> I am constantly worried that Gulool Ja may suffer some serious injury.
Why, just the other day, one of his scales was almost ripped clean off. Our swordsman-in-training laughed it off, but would that I could bear his pain for him...
As I mentioned, this next journey of mine will be a long one. Discovering all that is yet undiscovered on Etheirys will be the work of centuries.
And for the first time, I feel strangely nervous and eager to set sail. I think now I understand a little of how you felt when you boarded the ship for Tural.
Ha! Yaaagh! Master the basics! No wasted movement! Become one with the blade!
Though it was a hard decision to make, I finally went through with the restoration... It was the memories of my late mother that came first, one after another after another.
When I die someday, these things that only I remember of her may fade away, but without them─without the life we lived together─I would never fully be myself.
